/*
:name: adv_unknown_bits_11
:type: comptime
:verifier_pass: 4
:verifier_fail: 0
*/

// Per 04-variables.md: `a case b` requires every DEFINED bit of `b` to match
// `a`; only ? bits are wildcards. When a known bit of the pattern contradicts
// the value, `case` must be false (and `not(case)` true).
cassert(not (0ub1101 case 0ub10??))   // pattern needs bit2=0, value has bit2=1
cassert(not (0ub0011 case 0ub10??))   // pattern needs bit3=1, value has bit3=0
cassert(not (0ub1011 case 0ub0???))   // pattern needs bit3=0, value has bit3=1
cassert(not (0ub1111 case 0ub0??0))   // bit3 and bit0 both mismatch
